</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1848,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
Body yellowish brown to brown, transverse band on anterior margin of crown and on margins of pronotum, mesonotum and scutellum, ivory (
<figureCitation box="[542,716,1920,1945]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig 1. A, C, H</figureCitation>
). Face dark brown with broad ivory transverse band in middle below eyes (
<figureCitation box="[294,393,1956,1981]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig 1. B</figureCitation>
). Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[539,666,1956,1981]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig 1. E, F</figureCitation>
) with veins dark brown with whitish callosities; subcostal vein and apex of radial vein with dark stripe. Female with indistinct pale transverse medial band across forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1424,1992,2017]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Fig 1. H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
