<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1334]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">
Head slightly wider than pronotum. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[719,896,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. A, C, H</figureCitation>
) transversely broad; coronal suture (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1428,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. D</figureCitation>
) distinct; median length approximately a quarter as long as next to eyes; transversely concave subapically, with dense longitudinal wrinkles; concave next to eyes with oblique wrinkles. Ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1194,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. D</figureCitation>
) situated on anterior margin of head, visible dorsally; distance to adjacent eyes approximately 2.5 times ocellar diameter; laterofrontal sutures (
<figureCitation box="[245,371,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. B, D</figureCitation>
) reaching corresponding ocelli. Face (
<figureCitation box="[800,892,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. B</figureCitation>
) wider than long; frontoclypeus slightly swollen laterally; broad basally and narrow apically; frontoclypeal suture present; anteclypellus with median longitudinal carina, clypeal suture curved with apex slightly broader than base; gena (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1123,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. B</figureCitation>
) broad with disc concave, sparsely punctuate. Pronotum shorter than exposed part of mesonotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1264,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. C</figureCitation>
), with anterior margin arched; lateral margin short; hind margin concave, with dense wrinkles. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1301,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. E, F</figureCitation>
) crimped at apex of clavus, with four apical cells and three anteapical cells; appendix broad and extending to the wing apex. Profemur (
<figureCitation box="[275,378,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 1. G</figureCitation>
) with intercalary (IC) row represented by irregular band of fine setae; AM 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1260,1268,526,540]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">1</subScript>
seta enlarged, situated near apex. Metafemur with apical setal formula 2+1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1334]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[364,483,586,611]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. J, K</figureCitation>
) side moderately long and triangular without posterior process; tapering distally, with several macrosetae. Valve (
<figureCitation box="[462,635,622,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. K, L, M</figureCitation>
) semicircular. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1204,622,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. J, K, L, M</figureCitation>
) long; wide basally, tapering distally and sharply curved dorsad; with numerous short fine hair-like microsetae arising from lateral margin, irregularly arranged. Style (
<figureCitation box="[555,757,694,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. K, L, M, N</figureCitation>
) apical process elongate and digitate; lateral lobe prominent process with microsetae. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[588,689,730,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. O</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped; stem slender and arms robust; stem about as long as anterolateral arms, bifurcate apically. Aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[784,988,766,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. J, P, Q, R</figureCitation>
) curved dorsad, with pair of elongate laterobasal processes extending along shaft nearly to apex of shaft; gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1141,802,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. P, Q</figureCitation>
) apical on ventral surface. Segment X (
<figureCitation box="[291,377,838,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,195,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. J–R Male genitalia of D. stilliformis sp. nov.; J, Genital capsule, left lateral view; K, Genital capsule, ventral view; L, Valve, subgenital plate, style, connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; M, Valve, subgenital plate and style, dorsal view; N, Left style, ventral view; O, Connective, ventral view; P–R, Aedeagus, dorsal, posterior and left lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610674/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Fig 2. J</figureCitation>
) short, sclerotized laterally and dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1334]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">
Female genitalia. Hind margin of 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[606,618,874,888]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">th</superScript>
sternite (
<figureCitation box="[728,818,877,902]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">
Fig 
<date box="[777,818,878,902]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">1. I</date>
</figureCitation>
) with V-shaped notch and lateral margin truncate. 3 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1423,1436,874,888]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">rd</superScript>
valvulae (
<figureCitation box="[260,344,913,938]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[235,1353,202,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,193,1796]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–G Drabescus stilliformis sp. nov., male; A, Habitus, dorsal view; B, Face, ventral view; C, Head, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; D, Head, dorsoanterior view; E, Lateral view; F, Right forewing, dorsal view; G, Profemur, anterior view; H, D. stilliformis sp. nov., female, dorsal view; I, Female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2610672/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">
Fig 
<date box="[306,344,914,938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">1. I</date>
</figureCitation>
) slightly exceeding apex of pygofer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
