<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="477" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1334]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1165,1190]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species epithet originates from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[1035,1091,1165,1189]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">stilla</emphasis>
” for “drop”, referring to the pronotum and scutellum being surrounded by a drop-shaped ivory band.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="477" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1334]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1237,1262]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Webb, 1996" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Webb" authorityYear="1996" box="[666,1049,1237,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilbastei">
<emphasis box="[666,796,1237,1261]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">D. vilbastei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[804,1049,1237,1262]" pageId="4" pageNumber="477" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref4729" refString="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D. (1996) A revised classification of the Asian and Pacific selenocephaline leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum Entomology Series, 65, 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1996">Zhang &amp; Webb, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from the latter by the pygofer side without process (processes present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Webb" authorityYear="1996" box="[882,1013,1273,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilbastei">
<emphasis box="[882,902,1274,1297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[918,1013,1273,1297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">vilbastei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); style lateral lobe more pronounced and aedeagus with laterobasal processes nearly as long as the shaft (processes shorter than shaft in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Webb" authorityYear="1996" box="[1258,1387,1309,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vilbastei">
<emphasis box="[1258,1278,1310,1333]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1292,1387,1309,1333]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="477">vilbastei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
